abstract = {The Internet of Things (IoT) is an up and coming technology in the field of information and communication sciences. In the healthcare sector, a sizable number of IoT devices have been developed for diagnosing, monitoring, forecasting, and treatment of chronic diseases remotely. The sensors are to obtain important body parameters such as blood pressure, temperature, heart rate, and breath acetone store the data in the cloud repositories for healthcare professionals. The use of these devices referred to as smart sensors is becoming acceptable in smart healthcare for diagnosing and treatment of diseases as a result of the technological development of the needed devices. The data generated by these devices is huge and requires standard infrastructure to cope with the processing and transmissions. Edge computing technology tends to provide the required solution to smart sensor device processing and computational difficulties in smart healthcare by increase the communication and computational speed of the smart sensors with its cost-effective and low latency data services. The data transmitted by the smart sensor in smart healthcare systems (SHS) are personal that require confidentiality, integrity, and availability for prompt and correct decisions to be taken by the healthcare professionals, thus the data needed to be transmitted and stored securely. Therefore this paper proposes a lightweight Speck encryption algorithm for medical data from SHS. The proposed algorithm is applied to decrease the time for encryption in the SHS platform and to preserve the trade-off between security and efficiency. The proposed work is compared with recent works on lightweight start-ups in terms of accuracy, memory use, execution time, and precision. Results show that in an IoT-edge computing-driven setup, the algorithm is highly secure, efficient, and more suitable for securing data.}
}
@incollection{ACHARYA20223,
